## Context
Before adapting figures or polishing the companion paper, we need to know
whether the existing pipeline supports the NCC deliverables cleanly or
needs reorganization. The project has four Quarto outputs sharing includes,
a Phase 2 analysis pipeline, and Makefile targets for each output. A new
NCC piece may need its own Quarto document, figure targets, and vars file.

## Actions
1. Map which existing scripts/figures the NCC piece would reuse
2. Check if current Makefile targets cover the NCC figures or need new ones
3. Assess whether the companion paper build (make output/content/companion-paper.pdf)
   works cleanly today
4. Identify any shared includes that need NCC-specific variants vs reuse as-is
5. Decide: does the NCC piece live in content/ as a 5th Quarto output, or
   as a standalone document outside the Quarto project?
6. Flag any reorganization needed before execution tickets start

## Test
Written assessment in docs/ or as a note on the ticket.

## Exit criteria
Clear decision on pipeline architecture for the NCC deliverables.
Reorganization tasks (if any) identified and ticketed or folded into 0015/0018.
